cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with stochastic optimal control problem for systems with state dynamics governed by Partial Differential Equations (PDEs). 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a black box simulation model of the dynamical system and input-output experimental data consisting of the impulse responses of the optimized nominal system to design a Linear Quadratic Gaussian (LQG) controller. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper solves an open-loop deterministic trajectory optimization problem for the system. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses a computational nonlinear heat example to illustrate the performance of the approach. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a data-driven approach to design the controller for the system.
